{"parse":{"title":"List of first minority male lawyers and judges in Alabama","pageid":57635163,"revid":848295487,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>This is a list of the <b>first minority male lawyer(s) and judge(s)</b> in Alabama. It includes the year in which the men were admitted to practice law (in parentheses). Also included are other distinctions such as the first minority men in their state to obtain a law degree or become a political figure.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Firsts_in_state_history\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Firsts in state history</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Firsts_in_local_history\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Firsts in local history</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Firsts_in_state_history\">Firsts in state history</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=List_of_first_minority_male_lawyers_and_judges_in_Alabama&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Firsts in state history\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/R._C._O._Benjamin\" title=\"R. C. O. Benjamin\">R. C. O. Benjamin</a> (1880):<sup id=\"cite_ref-:60_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:60-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-:61_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:61-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> First African-American male lawyer in Alabama</li>\n<li>Roderick B. Thomas: First African-American judge in Alabama (1874)<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Oscar_Adams\" title=\"Oscar Adams\">Oscar Adams</a> (1947): First African-American justice of the <a href=\"/wiki/Alabama_Supreme_Court\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Alabama Supreme Court\">Alabama Supreme Court</a> (1980)<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/U._W._Clemon\" title=\"U. W. Clemon\">U. W. Clemon</a> (1968): First black <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_federal_judge\" title=\"United States federal judge\">United States federal judge</a> in Alabama<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Cain James Kennedy (1971): First African-American male appointed as a circuit judge in Alabama (1979)<sup id=\"cite_ref-:4_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-:4-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Firsts_in_local_history\">Firsts in local history</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=List_of_first_minority_male_lawyers_and_judges_in_Alabama&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Firsts in local history\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><i>Alphabetized by county name</i>\n</p>\n<ul><li>J.L. Chestnut (1958):<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup> First African-American male lawyer in Selma, Alabama <a href=\"/wiki/Dallas_County,_Alabama\" title=\"Dallas County, Alabama\">Dallas County, Alabama</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=List_of_first_minority_male_lawyers_and_judges_in_Alabama&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/List_of_first_minority_male_lawyers_and_judges_in_the_United_States\" title=\"List of first minority male lawyers and judges in the United States\">List of first minority male lawyers and judges in the United States</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=List_of_first_minority_male_lawyers_and_judges_in_Alabama&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-:60-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-:60_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.kentucky.com/news/local/counties/fayette-county/article44404029.html\">\"Black History Month: The life of Robert Charles O'Hara Benjamin\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Lexington_Herald-Leader\" title=\"Lexington Herald-Leader\">Lexington Herald-Leader</a></i>. February 16, 2013.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Lexington+Herald-Leader&amp;rft.atitle=Black+History+Month%3A+The+life+of+Robert+Charles+O%27Hara+Benjamin&amp;rft.date=2013-02-16&amp;rf